    <constitutionalAuthorityStatementText><![CDATA[<pre>[Congressional Record Volume 172, Number 49 (Wednesday, March 18, 2026)][House]From the Congressional Record Online through the Government Publishing Office [<a href="https://www.gpo.gov">www.gpo.gov</a>]By Mr. SWALWELL:H.R. 7988.Congress has the power to enact this legislation pursuantto the following:This bill is grounded in Congress's authority under ArticleI, Section 9, Clause 7 of the U.S. Constitution(Appropriations Clause), which allows Congress to control howfederal funds are spent. It also relies on the Necessary andProper Clause (Article I, Section 8, Clause 18) to structurehow federal agencies carry out enforcement activities.[Page H2597]</pre>]]></constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>
